(654,6,'DALL·E now available in beta','We’ll invite 1 million people from our waitlist over the coming weeks. Users can create with DALL·E using free credits that refill every month, and buy additional credits in 115-generation increments for $15.','https://openai.com/index/dall-e-now-available-in-beta','','2026-01-31 11:07:01','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[DALL\\u00b7E now available in beta]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ll invite 1 million people from our waitlist over the coming weeks. Users can create with DALL\\u00b7E using free credits that refill every month, and buy additional credits in 115-generation increments for\\u00a0$15.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/dall-e-now-available-in-beta<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/dall-e-now-available-in-beta<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Product]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',44.50,7,20.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:07:01'),
(655,6,'Reducing bias and improving safety in DALL·E 2','Today, we are implementing a new technique so that DALL·E generates images of people that more accurately reflect the diversity of the world’s population.','https://openai.com/index/reducing-bias-and-improving-safety-in-dall-e-2','','2026-01-31 11:04:42','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Reducing bias and improving safety in DALL\\u00b7E 2]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Today, we are implementing a new technique so that DALL\\u00b7E generates images of people that more accurately reflect the diversity of the world\\u2019s population.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/reducing-bias-and-improving-safety-in-dall-e-2<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/reducing-bias-and-improving-safety-in-dall-e-2<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Product]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 18 Jul 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.25,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:04:42'),
(656,6,'DALL·E 2: Extending creativity','As part of our DALL·E 2 research preview, more than 3,000 artists from more than 118 countries have incorporated DALL·E into their creative workflows. The artists in our early access group have helped us discover new uses for DALL·E and have served as key voices as we’ve made decisions about DALL·E’s features.','https://openai.com/index/dall-e-2-extending-creativity','','2022-07-14 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[DALL\\u00b7E 2: Extending creativity]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[As part of our DALL\\u00b7E 2 research preview, more than 3,000 artists from more than 118 countries have incorporated DALL\\u00b7E into their creative workflows. The artists in our early access group have helped us discover new uses for DALL\\u00b7E and have served as key voices as we\\u2019ve made decisions about DALL\\u00b7E\\u2019s\\u00a0features.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/dall-e-2-extending-creativity<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/dall-e-2-extending-creativity<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 14 Jul 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',34.08,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(657,6,'DALL·E 2 pre-training mitigations','In order to share the magic of DALL·E 2 with a broad audience, we needed to reduce the risks associated with powerful image generation models. To this end, we put various guardrails in place to prevent generated images from violating our content policy.','https://openai.com/index/dall-e-2-pre-training-mitigations','','2022-06-28 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[DALL\\u00b7E 2 pre-training mitigations]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[In order to share the magic of\\u00a0DALL\\u00b7E 2\\u00a0with a broad audience, we needed to reduce the risks associated with powerful image generation models. To this end, we put various\\u00a0guardrails\\u00a0in place to prevent generated images from violating our\\u00a0content policy.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/dall-e-2-pre-training-mitigations<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/dall-e-2-pre-training-mitigations<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jun 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',31.76,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(658,6,'Learning to play Minecraft with Video PreTraining','We trained a neural network to play Minecraft by Video PreTraining (VPT) on a massive unlabeled video dataset of human Minecraft play, while using only a small amount of labeled contractor data. With fine-tuning, our model can learn to craft diamond tools, a task that usually takes proficient humans over 20 minutes (24,000 actions). Our model uses the native human interface of keypresses and mouse movements, making it quite general, and represents a step towards general computer-using agents.','https://openai.com/index/vpt','','2022-06-23 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Learning to play Minecraft with Video PreTraining]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We trained a neural network to play Minecraft by Video PreTraining (VPT) on a massive unlabeled video dataset of human Minecraft play, while using only a small amount of labeled contractor data. With fine-tuning, our model can learn to craft diamond tools, a task that usually takes proficient humans over 20 minutes (24,000 actions). Our model uses the native human interface of keypresses and mouse movements, making it quite general, and represents a step towards general computer-using\\u00a0agents.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/vpt<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/vpt<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jun 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(659,6,'Evolution through large models','','https://openai.com/index/evolution-through-large-models','','2026-01-31 10:50:33','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Evolution through large models]]><\\/title>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/evolution-through-large-models<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/evolution-through-large-models<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jun 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.50,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:33'),
(660,6,'AI-written critiques help humans notice flaws','We trained “critique-writing” models to describe flaws in summaries. Human evaluators find flaws in summaries much more often when shown our model’s critiques. Larger models are better at self-critiquing, with scale improving critique-writing more than summary-writing. This shows promise for using AI systems to assist human supervision of AI systems on difficult tasks.','https://openai.com/index/critiques','','2022-06-13 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[AI-written critiques help humans notice flaws]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We trained \\u201ccritique-writing\\u201d models to describe flaws in summaries. Human evaluators find flaws in summaries much more often when shown our model\\u2019s critiques. Larger models are better at self-critiquing, with scale improving critique-writing more than summary-writing. This shows promise for using AI systems to assist human supervision of AI systems on difficult\\u00a0tasks.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/critiques<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/critiques<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jun 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.49,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(661,6,'Techniques for training large neural networks','Large neural networks are at the core of many recent advances in AI, but training them is a difficult engineering and research challenge which requires orchestrating a cluster of GPUs to perform a single synchronized calculation.','https://openai.com/index/techniques-for-training-large-neural-networks','','2022-06-09 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Techniques for training large neural networks]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Large neural networks are at the core of many recent advances in AI, but training them is a difficult engineering and research challenge which requires orchestrating a cluster of GPUs to perform a single synchronized calculation.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/techniques-for-training-large-neural-networks<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/techniques-for-training-large-neural-networks<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 09 Jun 2022 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',34.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
