(694,6,'Scaling Kubernetes to 7,500 nodes','We’ve scaled Kubernetes clusters to 7,500 nodes, producing a scalable infrastructure for large models like GPT-3, CLIP, and DALL·E, but also for rapid small-scale iterative research such as Scaling Laws for Neural Language Models.','https://openai.com/index/scaling-kubernetes-to-7500-nodes','','2021-01-25 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Scaling Kubernetes to 7,500 nodes]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve scaled Kubernetes clusters to 7,500 nodes, producing a scalable infrastructure for large models like\\u00a0GPT-3,\\u00a0CLIP, and\\u00a0DALL\\u00b7E, but also for rapid small-scale iterative research such as\\u00a0Scaling Laws for Neural Language Models.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/scaling-kubernetes-to-7500-nodes<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/scaling-kubernetes-to-7500-nodes<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 25 Jan 2021 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',30.84,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
