(705,6,'Language models are few-shot learners','','https://openai.com/index/language-models-are-few-shot-learners','','2026-01-31 10:50:34','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Language models are few-shot learners]]><\\/title>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/language-models-are-few-shot-learners<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/language-models-are-few-shot-learners<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2020 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.50,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:34'),
(706,6,'AI and efficiency','We’re releasing an analysis showing that since 2012 the amount of compute needed to train a neural net to the same performance on ImageNet classification has been decreasing by a factor of 2 every 16 months. Compared to 2012, it now takes 44 times less compute to train a neural network to the level of AlexNet (by contrast, Moore’s Law would yield an 11x cost improvement over this period). Our results suggest that for AI tasks with high levels of recent investment, algorithmic progress has yielded more gains than classical hardware efficiency.','https://openai.com/index/ai-and-efficiency','','2020-05-05 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[AI and efficiency]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing an analysis showing that since 2012 the amount of compute needed to train a neural net to the same performance on ImageNet\\u00a0classification has been decreasing by a factor of 2 every 16 months. Compared to 2012, it now takes 44 times less compute to train a neural network to the level of AlexNet\\u00a0(by contrast, Moore\\u2019s Law\\u00a0would yield an 11x cost improvement over this period). Our results suggest that for AI tasks with high levels of recent investment, algorithmic progress has yielded more gains than classical hardware\\u00a0efficiency.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/ai-and-efficiency<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/ai-and-efficiency<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2020 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(707,6,'Jukebox','We’re introducing Jukebox, a neural net that generates music, including rudimentary singing, as raw audio in a variety of genres and artist styles. We’re releasing the model weights and code, along with a tool to explore the generated samples.','https://openai.com/index/jukebox','','2020-04-30 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Jukebox]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re introducing Jukebox, a neural net that generates music, including rudimentary singing, as raw audio in a variety of genres and artist styles. We\\u2019re releasing the model weights and code, along with a tool to explore the generated\\u00a0samples.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/jukebox<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/jukebox<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2020 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',30.24,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(708,6,'Improving verifiability in AI development','We’ve contributed to a multi-stakeholder report by 58 co-authors at 30 organizations, including the Centre for the Future of Intelligence, Mila, Schwartz Reisman Institute for Technology and Society, Center for Advanced Study in the Behavioral Sciences, and Center for Security and Emerging Technologies. This report describes 10 mechanisms to improve the verifiability of claims made about AI systems. Developers can use these tools to provide evidence that AI systems are safe, secure, fair, or privacy-preserving. Users, policymakers, and civil society can use these tools to evaluate AI development processes.','https://openai.com/index/improving-verifiability','','2020-04-16 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Improving verifiability in AI development]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve contributed to a multi-stakeholder report by\\u00a058 co-authors\\u00a0at 30 organizations, including the\\u00a0Centre for the Future of Intelligence,\\u00a0Mila,\\u00a0Schwartz Reisman Institute for Technology and Society,\\u00a0Center for Advanced Study in the Behavioral Sciences, and\\u00a0Center for Security and Emerging Technologies. This report describes 10 mechanisms to improve the verifiability of claims made about AI systems. Developers can use these tools to provide evidence that AI systems are safe, secure, fair, or privacy-preserving. Users, policymakers, and civil society can use these tools to evaluate AI development\\u00a0processes.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/improving-verifiability<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/improving-verifiability<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2020 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(709,6,'OpenAI Microscope','We’re introducing OpenAI Microscope, a collection of visualizations of every significant layer and neuron of eight vision “model organisms” which are often studied in interpretability. Microscope makes it easier to analyze the features that form inside these neural networks, and we hope it will help the research community as we move towards understanding these complicated systems.','https://openai.com/index/microscope','','2020-04-14 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Microscope]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re introducing\\u00a0OpenAI Microscope, a collection of visualizations of every significant layer and neuron of eight vision \\u201cmodel organisms\\u201d which are often studied in interpretability. Microscope makes it easier to analyze the features that form inside these neural networks, and we hope it will help the research community as we move towards understanding these complicated\\u00a0systems.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/microscope<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/microscope<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2020 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',36.36,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(710,6,'OpenAI standardizes on PyTorch','We are standardizing OpenAI’s deep learning framework on PyTorch.','https://openai.com/index/openai-pytorch','','2026-01-31 10:50:34','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI standardizes on PyTorch]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We are standardizing OpenAI\\u2019s deep learning framework on\\u00a0PyTorch.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-pytorch<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-pytorch<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 30 Jan 2020 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',52.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:34'),
