(713,6,'Deep double descent','We show that the double descent phenomenon occurs in CNNs, ResNets, and transformers: performance first improves, then gets worse, and then improves again with increasing model size, data size, or training time. This effect is often avoided through careful regularization. While this behavior appears to be fairly universal, we don’t yet fully understand why it happens, and view further study of this phenomenon as an important research direction.','https://openai.com/index/deep-double-descent','','2019-12-05 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Deep double descent]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We show that the\\u00a0double\\u00a0descent\\u00a0phenomenon\\u00a0occurs in CNNs, ResNets, and transformers: performance first improves, then gets worse, and then improves again with increasing model size, data size, or training time. This effect is often avoided through careful regularization. While this behavior appears to be fairly universal, we don\\u2019t yet fully understand why it happens, and view further study of this phenomenon as an important research\\u00a0direction.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/deep-double-descent<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/deep-double-descent<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 05 Dec 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',39.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(714,6,'Procgen Benchmark','We’re releasing Procgen Benchmark, 16 simple-to-use procedurally-generated environments which provide a direct measure of how quickly a reinforcement learning agent learns generalizable skills.','https://openai.com/index/procgen-benchmark','','2019-12-03 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Procgen Benchmark]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing Procgen Benchmark, 16 simple-to-use\\u00a0procedurally-generated\\u00a0environments which provide a direct measure of how quickly a reinforcement learning agent learns generalizable\\u00a0skills.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/procgen-benchmark<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/procgen-benchmark<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 03 Dec 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',32.17,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(715,6,'Safety Gym','We’re releasing Safety Gym, a suite of environments and tools for measuring progress towards reinforcement learning agents that respect safety constraints while training.','https://openai.com/index/safety-gym','','2019-11-21 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Safety Gym]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing Safety Gym, a suite of environments and tools for measuring progress towards reinforcement learning agents that respect safety constraints while\\u00a0training.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/safety-gym<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/safety-gym<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 21 Nov 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',30.89,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(716,6,'Benchmarking safe exploration in deep reinforcement learning','','https://openai.com/index/benchmarking-safe-exploration-in-deep-reinforcement-learning','','2026-01-31 10:50:34','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Benchmarking safe exploration in deep reinforcement learning]]><\\/title>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/benchmarking-safe-exploration-in-deep-reinforcement-learning<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/benchmarking-safe-exploration-in-deep-reinforcement-learning<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 21 Nov 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.50,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:34'),
(717,6,'GPT-2: 1.5B release','As the final model release of GPT-2’s staged release, we’re releasing the largest version (1.5B parameters) of GPT-2 along with code and model weights to facilitate detection of outputs of GPT-2 models. While there have been larger language models released since August, we’ve continued with our original staged release plan in order to provide the community with a test case of a full staged release process. We hope that this test case will be useful to developers of future powerful models, and we’re actively continuing the conversation with the AI community on responsible publication.','https://openai.com/index/gpt-2-1-5b-release','','2019-11-05 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[GPT-2: 1.5B release]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[As the final model release of\\u00a0GPT-2\\u2019s\\u00a0staged release, we\\u2019re releasing the largest version (1.5B parameters) of GPT-2 along with\\u00a0code and model weights\\u00a0to facilitate detection of outputs of GPT-2 models. While there have been larger language models released since August, we\\u2019ve continued with our original staged release plan in order to provide the community with a test case of a full staged release process. We hope that this test case will be useful to developers of future powerful models, and we\\u2019re actively continuing the conversation with the AI community on responsible\\u00a0publication.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/gpt-2-1-5b-release<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/gpt-2-1-5b-release<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 05 Nov 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',47.06,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(718,6,'Solving Rubik’s Cube with a robot hand','We’ve trained a pair of neural networks to solve the Rubik’s Cube with a human-like robot hand. The neural networks are trained entirely in simulation, using the same reinforcement learning code as OpenAI Five paired with a new technique called Automatic Domain Randomization (ADR). The system can handle situations it never saw during training, such as being prodded by a stuffed giraffe. This shows that reinforcement learning isn’t just a tool for virtual tasks, but can solve physical-world problems requiring unprecedented dexterity.','https://openai.com/index/solving-rubiks-cube','','2019-10-15 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Solving Rubik\\u2019s Cube with a robot hand]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve trained a pair of neural networks to solve the Rubik\\u2019s Cube with a human-like robot hand. The neural networks are trained entirely in simulation, using the same reinforcement learning code as\\u00a0OpenAI Five\\u00a0paired with a new technique called Automatic Domain Randomization (ADR). The system can handle situations it never saw during training, such as being prodded by a\\u00a0stuffed giraffe. This shows that reinforcement learning isn\\u2019t just a tool for virtual tasks, but can solve physical-world problems requiring unprecedented dexterity.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/solving-rubiks-cube<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/solving-rubiks-cube<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 15 Oct 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(719,6,'OpenAI Scholars 2020: Applications open','We are now accepting applications for our third class of OpenAI Scholars.','https://openai.com/index/openai-scholars-2020','','2026-01-31 10:54:46','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Scholars 2020: Applications open]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We are now accepting applications for our third class of OpenAI Scholars.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2020<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2020<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Fri, 11 Oct 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',24.52,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'rejected',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:54:46'),
(720,6,'Fine-tuning GPT-2 from human preferences','We’ve fine-tuned the 774M parameter GPT-2 language model using human feedback for various tasks, successfully matching the preferences of the external human labelers, though those preferences did not always match our own. Specifically, for summarization tasks the labelers preferred sentences copied wholesale from the input (we’d only asked them to ensure accuracy), so our models learned to copy. Summarization required 60k human labels; simpler tasks which continue text in various styles required only 5k. Our motivation is to move safety techniques closer to the general task of “machines talking to humans,” which we believe is key to extracting information about human values.','https://openai.com/index/fine-tuning-gpt-2','','2019-09-19 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Fine-tuning GPT-2 from human preferences]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve fine-tuned the 774M parameter GPT-2 language model using human feedback for various tasks, successfully matching the preferences of the external human labelers, though those preferences did not always match our own. Specifically, for summarization tasks the labelers preferred sentences copied wholesale from the input (we\\u2019d only asked them to ensure accuracy), so our models learned to copy. Summarization required 60k human labels; simpler tasks which continue text in various styles required only 5k. Our motivation is to move safety techniques closer to the general task of \\u201cmachines talking to humans,\\u201d which we believe is key to extracting information about human\\u00a0values.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/fine-tuning-gpt-2<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/fine-tuning-gpt-2<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 19 Sep 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(721,6,'Emergent tool use from multi-agent interaction','We’ve observed agents discovering progressively more complex tool use while playing a simple game of hide-and-seek. Through training in our new simulated hide-and-seek environment, agents build a series of six distinct strategies and counterstrategies, some of which we did not know our environment supported. The self-supervised emergent complexity in this simple environment further suggests that multi-agent co-adaptation may one day produce extremely complex and intelligent behavior.','https://openai.com/index/emergent-tool-use','','2019-09-17 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Emergent tool use from multi-agent interaction]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve observed agents discovering progressively more complex tool use while playing a simple game of hide-and-seek. Through training in our new simulated hide-and-seek environment, agents build a series of six distinct strategies and counterstrategies, some of which we did not know our environment supported. The self-supervised emergent complexity in this simple environment further suggests that multi-agent co-adaptation may one day produce extremely complex and intelligent behavior.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/emergent-tool-use<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/emergent-tool-use<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 17 Sep 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(722,6,'Testing robustness against unforeseen adversaries','We’ve developed a method to assess whether a neural network classifier can reliably defend against adversarial attacks not seen during training. Our method yields a new metric, UAR (Unforeseen Attack Robustness), which evaluates the robustness of a single model against an unanticipated attack, and highlights the need to measure performance across a more diverse range of unforeseen attacks.','https://openai.com/index/testing-robustness','','2019-08-22 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Testing robustness against unforeseen adversaries]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve developed a method to assess whether a neural network classifier can reliably defend against adversarial attacks not seen during training. Our method yields a new metric, UAR (Unforeseen Attack Robustness), which evaluates the robustness of a single model against an unanticipated attack, and highlights the need to measure performance across a more diverse range of unforeseen\\u00a0attacks.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/testing-robustness<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/testing-robustness<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 22 Aug 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',37.80,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(723,6,'GPT-2: 6-month follow-up','We’re releasing the 774 million parameter GPT-2 language model after the release of our small 124M model in February, staged release of our medium 355M model in May, and subsequent research with partners and the AI community into the model’s potential for misuse and societal benefit. We’re also releasing an open-source legal agreement to make it easier for organizations to initiate model-sharing partnerships with each other, and are publishing a technical report about our experience in coordinating with the wider AI research community on publication norms.','https://openai.com/index/gpt-2-6-month-follow-up','','2019-08-20 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[GPT-2: 6-month follow-up]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing the 774 million parameter GPT-2 language model after the release of our small\\u00a0124M model\\u00a0in February, staged release of our medium\\u00a0355M model\\u00a0in May, and subsequent research with partners and the AI community into the model\\u2019s potential for misuse and societal benefit. We\\u2019re also releasing an open-source legal agreement to make it easier for organizations to initiate model-sharing partnerships with each other, and are publishing a technical report about our experience in coordinating with the wider AI research community on publication\\u00a0norms.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/gpt-2-6-month-follow-up<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/gpt-2-6-month-follow-up<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(724,6,'Learning Day','At OpenAI, each Thursday is Learning Day: a day where employees have the option to self-study technical skills that will make them better at their job but which aren’t being learned from daily work.','https://openai.com/index/learning-day','','2026-01-31 11:06:57','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Learning Day]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[At OpenAI, each Thursday is Learning Day: a day where employees have the option to self-study technical skills that will make them better at their job but which aren\\u2019t being learned from daily work.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-day<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-day<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 01 Aug 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',47.00,7,40.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:06:57'),
(725,6,'Microsoft invests in and partners with OpenAI to support us building beneficial AGI','Microsoft is investing $1 billion in OpenAI to support us building artificial general intelligence (AGI) with widely distributed economic benefits. We’re partnering to develop a hardware and software platform within Microsoft Azure which will scale to AGI. We’ll jointly develop new Azure AI supercomputing technologies, and Microsoft will become our exclusive cloud provider—so we’ll be working hard together to further extend Microsoft Azure’s capabilities in large-scale AI systems.','https://openai.com/index/microsoft-invests-in-and-partners-with-openai','','2019-07-22 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Microsoft invests in and partners with OpenAI to support us building beneficial AGI]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Microsoft is investing $1 billion in OpenAI to support us building artificial general intelligence (AGI) with widely distributed economic benefits. We\\u2019re partnering to develop a hardware and software platform within Microsoft Azure which will scale to AGI. We\\u2019ll jointly develop new Azure AI supercomputing technologies, and Microsoft will become our exclusive cloud provider\\u2014so we\\u2019ll be working hard together to further extend Microsoft Azure\\u2019s capabilities in large-scale AI systems.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/microsoft-invests-in-and-partners-with-openai<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/microsoft-invests-in-and-partners-with-openai<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 22 Jul 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(726,6,'Why responsible AI development needs cooperation on safety','We’ve written a policy research paper identifying four strategies that can be used today to improve the likelihood of long-term industry cooperation on safety norms in AI: communicating risks and benefits, technical collaboration, increased transparency, and incentivizing standards. Our analysis shows that industry cooperation on safety will be instrumental in ensuring that AI systems are safe and beneficial, but competitive pressures could lead to a collective action problem, potentially causing AI companies to under-invest in safety. We hope these strategies will encourage greater cooperation on the safe development of AI and lead to better global outcomes of AI.','https://openai.com/index/cooperation-on-safety','','2019-07-10 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Why responsible AI development needs cooperation on safety]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve written a policy research paper identifying four strategies that can be used today to improve the likelihood of long-term industry cooperation on safety norms in AI: communicating risks and benefits, technical collaboration, increased transparency, and incentivizing standards. Our analysis shows that industry cooperation on safety will be instrumental in ensuring that AI systems are safe and beneficial, but competitive pressures could lead to a collective action problem, potentially causing AI companies to under-invest in safety. We hope these strategies will encourage greater cooperation on the safe development of AI and lead to better global outcomes of\\u00a0AI.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/cooperation-on-safety<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/cooperation-on-safety<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(727,6,'OpenAI Robotics Symposium 2019','We hosted the first OpenAI Robotics Symposium on April 27, 2019.','https://openai.com/index/symposium-2019','','2026-01-31 10:50:34','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Robotics Symposium 2019]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We hosted the first OpenAI Robotics Symposium on April 27, 2019.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/symposium-2019<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/symposium-2019<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 05 Jun 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',48.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:34'),
(728,6,'OpenAI Scholars 2019: Final projects','Our second class of OpenAI Scholars has concluded, with all eight scholars producing an exciting final project showcased at Scholars Demo Day at OpenAI.','https://openai.com/index/openai-scholars-2019-final-projects','','2026-01-31 11:04:40','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Scholars 2019: Final projects]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Our second class of OpenAI Scholars has concluded, with all eight scholars producing an exciting final project showcased at Scholars Demo Day at OpenAI.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2019-final-projects<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2019-final-projects<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 23 May 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',27.56,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'rejected',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:04:40'),
(729,6,'OpenAI Fellows Fall 2018: Final projects','Our second class of OpenAI Fellows has wrapped up, with each Fellow going from a machine learning beginner to core OpenAI contributor in the course of a 6-month apprenticeship. We are currently reviewing applications on a rolling basis for our next round of OpenAI Fellows Summer 2019.','https://openai.com/index/openai-fellows-fall-2018','','2019-05-17 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Fellows Fall 2018: Final projects]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Our second class of OpenAI Fellows has wrapped up, with each Fellow going from a machine learning beginner to core OpenAI contributor in the course of a 6-month apprenticeship. We are currently reviewing applications on a rolling basis for our next round of OpenAI Fellows Summer 2019.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-fellows-fall-2018<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-fellows-fall-2018<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Fri, 17 May 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',33.04,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(730,6,'Transfer of adversarial robustness between perturbation types','','https://openai.com/index/transfer-of-adversarial-robustness-between-perturbation-types','','2026-01-31 10:50:34','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Transfer of adversarial robustness between perturbation types]]><\\/title>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/transfer-of-adversarial-robustness-between-perturbation-types<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/transfer-of-adversarial-robustness-between-perturbation-types<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Fri, 03 May 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',41.50,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:34'),
(731,6,'MuseNet','We’ve created MuseNet, a deep neural network that can generate 4-minute musical compositions with 10 different instruments, and can combine styles from country to Mozart to the Beatles. MuseNet was not explicitly programmed with our understanding of music, but instead discovered patterns of harmony, rhythm, and style by learning to predict the next token in hundreds of thousands of MIDI files. MuseNet uses the same general-purpose unsupervised technology as GPT-2, a large-scale transformer model trained to predict the next token in a sequence, whether audio or text.','https://openai.com/index/musenet','','2019-04-25 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[MuseNet]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve created MuseNet, a deep neural network that can generate 4-minute musical compositions with 10 different instruments, and can combine styles from country to Mozart to the Beatles. MuseNet was not explicitly programmed with our understanding of music, but instead discovered patterns of harmony, rhythm, and style by learning to predict the next token in hundreds of thousands of MIDI files. MuseNet uses the same general-purpose unsupervised technology as\\u00a0GPT-2, a large-scale\\u00a0transformer\\u00a0model trained to predict the next token in a sequence, whether audio or\\u00a0text.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/musenet<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/musenet<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 25 Apr 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(732,6,'Generative modeling with sparse transformers','We’ve developed the Sparse Transformer, a deep neural network which sets new records at predicting what comes next in a sequence—whether text, images, or sound. It uses an algorithmic improvement of the attention mechanism to extract patterns from sequences 30x longer than possible previously.','https://openai.com/index/sparse-transformer','','2019-04-23 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Generative modeling with sparse transformers]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve developed the Sparse Transformer, a deep neural network which sets new records at predicting what comes next in a sequence\\u2014whether text, images, or sound. It uses an algorithmic improvement of the\\u00a0attention\\u00a0mechanism to extract patterns from sequences 30x longer than possible\\u00a0previously.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/sparse-transformer<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/sparse-transformer<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 23 Apr 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',33.84,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(733,6,'OpenAI Five defeats Dota 2 world champions','OpenAI Five is the first AI to beat the world champions in an esports game, having won two back-to-back games versus the world champion Dota 2 team, OG, at Finals this weekend. Both OpenAI Five and DeepMind’s AlphaStar had previously beaten good pros privately but lost their live pro matches, making this also the first time an AI has beaten esports pros on livestream.','https://openai.com/index/openai-five-defeats-dota-2-world-champions','','2019-04-15 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Five defeats Dota 2 world champions]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[OpenAI Five is the first AI to beat the world champions in an esports game, having won two back-to-back games versus the world champion Dota 2 team,\\u00a0OG, at\\u00a0Finals\\u00a0this weekend. Both OpenAI Five and DeepMind\\u2019s AlphaStar had previously beaten good pros privately but lost their live pro matches, making this also the first time an AI has beaten esports pros on\\u00a0livestream.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-five-defeats-dota-2-world-champions<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-five-defeats-dota-2-world-champions<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 15 Apr 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',36.76,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(734,6,'OpenAI Five Finals','We’ll be holding our final live event for OpenAI Five at 11:30am PT on April 13.','https://openai.com/index/openai-five-finals','','2026-01-31 10:50:36','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Five Finals]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ll be holding our final live event for OpenAI Five at 11:30am PT on April 13.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-five-finals<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-five-finals<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 26 Mar 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',46.50,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:36'),
(735,6,'Implicit generation and generalization methods for energy-based models','We’ve made progress towards stable and scalable training of energy-based models (EBMs) resulting in better sample quality and generalization ability than existing models. Generation in EBMs spends more compute to continually refine its answers and doing so can generate samples competitive with GANs at low temperatures, while also having mode coverage guarantees of likelihood-based models. We hope these findings stimulate further research into this promising class of models.','https://openai.com/index/energy-based-models','','2019-03-21 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Implicit generation and generalization methods for energy-based models]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve made progress towards stable and scalable training of\\u00a0energy-based models\\u00a0(EBMs) resulting in better sample quality and generalization ability than existing models. Generation in EBMs spends more compute to continually refine its answers and doing so can generate samples competitive with\\u00a0GANs\\u00a0at low temperatures,\\u00a0while also having mode coverage guarantees of\\u00a0likelihood-based models. We hope these findings stimulate further research into this promising class of\\u00a0models.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/energy-based-models<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/energy-based-models<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 21 Mar 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(736,6,'OpenAI Scholars 2019: Meet our Scholars','Our class of eight scholars (out of 550 applicants) brings together collective expertise in literature, philosophy, cell biology, statistics, economics, quantum physics, and business innovation.','https://openai.com/index/openai-scholars-2019-meet-our-scholars','','2026-01-31 11:07:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Scholars 2019: Meet our Scholars]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Our class of eight\\u00a0scholars\\u00a0(out of 550 applicants) brings together collective expertise in literature, philosophy, cell biology, statistics, economics, quantum physics, and business innovation.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2019-meet-our-scholars<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2019-meet-our-scholars<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 13 Mar 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',29.44,NULL,0.00,1,761,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'rejected',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:07:00'),
(737,6,'OpenAI LP','We’ve created OpenAI LP, a new “capped-profit” company that allows us to rapidly increase our investments in compute and talent while including checks and balances to actualize our mission.','https://openai.com/index/openai-lp','','2026-01-31 11:04:42','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI LP]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve created OpenAI LP, a new \\u201ccapped-profit\\u201d company that allows us to rapidly increase our investments in compute and talent while including checks and balances to actualize our mission.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-lp<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-lp<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2019 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',47.75,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:04:42'),
(738,6,'Introducing Activation Atlases','We’ve created activation atlases (in collaboration with Google researchers), a new technique for visualizing what interactions between neurons can represent. As AI systems are deployed in increasingly sensitive contexts, having a better understanding of their internal decision-making processes will let us identify weaknesses and investigate failures.','https://openai.com/index/introducing-activation-atlases','','2019-03-06 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Introducing Activation Atlases]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve created\\u00a0activation atlases\\u00a0(in\\u00a0collaboration\\u00a0with Google researchers), a new technique for visualizing what interactions between neurons can represent. As AI systems are deployed in increasingly sensitive contexts, having a better understanding of their internal decision-making processes will let us identify weaknesses and investigate\\u00a0failures.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/introducing-activation-atlases<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/introducing-activation-atlases<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 06 Mar 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',35.60,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(739,6,'Neural MMO: A massively multiagent game environment','We’re releasing a Neural MMO, a massively multiagent game environment for reinforcement learning agents. Our platform supports a large, variable number of agents within a persistent and open-ended task. The inclusion of many agents and species leads to better exploration, divergent niche formation, and greater overall competence.','https://openai.com/index/neural-mmo','','2019-03-04 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Neural MMO: A massively multiagent game environment]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing a Neural\\u00a0MMO, a massively multiagent game environment for reinforcement learning agents. Our platform supports a large, variable number of agents within a persistent and open-ended task. The inclusion of many agents and species leads to better exploration, divergent niche formation, and greater overall\\u00a0competence.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/neural-mmo<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/neural-mmo<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 04 Mar 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',35.48,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(740,6,'Spinning Up in Deep RL: Workshop review','On February 2, we held our first Spinning Up Workshop as part of our new education initiative at OpenAI.','https://openai.com/index/spinning-up-in-deep-rl-workshop-review','','2026-01-31 10:58:16','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Spinning Up in Deep RL: Workshop review]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[On February 2, we held our first Spinning Up Workshop as part of our new education initiative at OpenAI.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/spinning-up-in-deep-rl-workshop-review<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/spinning-up-in-deep-rl-workshop-review<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 26 Feb 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',50.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:58:16'),
(741,6,'AI safety needs social scientists','We’ve written a paper arguing that long-term AI safety research needs social scientists to ensure AI alignment algorithms succeed when actual humans are involved. Properly aligning advanced AI systems with human values requires resolving many uncertainties related to the psychology of human rationality, emotion, and biases. The aim of this paper is to spark further collaboration between machine learning and social science researchers, and we plan to hire social scientists to work on this full time at OpenAI.','https://openai.com/index/ai-safety-needs-social-scientists','','2019-02-19 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[AI safety needs social scientists]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve written a paper arguing that long-term AI safety research needs social scientists to ensure AI alignment algorithms succeed when actual humans are involved. Properly aligning advanced AI systems with human values requires resolving many uncertainties related to the psychology of human rationality, emotion, and biases. The aim of this paper is to spark further collaboration between machine learning and social science researchers, and we plan to\\u00a0hire\\u00a0social scientists to work on this full time at\\u00a0OpenAI.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/ai-safety-needs-social-scientists<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/ai-safety-needs-social-scientists<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Tue, 19 Feb 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(742,6,'Better language models and their implications','We’ve trained a large-scale unsupervised language model which generates coherent paragraphs of text, achieves state-of-the-art performance on many language modeling benchmarks, and performs rudimentary reading comprehension, machine translation, question answering, and summarization—all without task-specific training.','https://openai.com/index/better-language-models','','2019-02-14 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Better language models and their implications]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve trained a large-scale unsupervised language model which generates coherent paragraphs of text, achieves state-of-the-art performance on many language modeling benchmarks, and performs rudimentary reading comprehension, machine translation, question answering, and summarization\\u2014all without task-specific\\u00a0training.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/better-language-models<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/better-language-models<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 14 Feb 2019 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',34.80,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
