(744,6,'OpenAI Fellows Summer 2018: Final projects','Our first cohort of OpenAI Fellows has concluded, with each Fellow going from a machine learning beginner to core OpenAI contributor in the course of a 6-month apprenticeship.','https://openai.com/index/openai-summer-fellows-2018','','2026-01-31 11:06:58','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Fellows Summer 2018: Final projects]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Our first cohort of OpenAI Fellows has concluded, with each Fellow going from a machine learning beginner to core OpenAI contributor in the course of a 6-month apprenticeship.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-summer-fellows-2018<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-summer-fellows-2018<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 19 Dec 2018 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',28.72,NULL,0.00,1,729,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'rejected',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 11:06:58'),
(745,6,'How AI training scales','We’ve discovered that the gradient noise scale, a simple statistical metric, predicts the parallelizability of neural network training on a wide range of tasks. Since complex tasks tend to have noisier gradients, increasingly large batch sizes are likely to become useful in the future, removing one potential limit to further growth of AI systems. More broadly, these results show that neural network training need not be considered a mysterious art, but can be rigorized and systematized.','https://openai.com/index/how-ai-training-scales','','2018-12-14 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[How AI training scales]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve discovered that the gradient noise scale, a simple statistical metric, predicts the parallelizability of neural network training on a wide range of tasks. Since complex tasks tend to have noisier gradients, increasingly large batch sizes are likely to become useful in the future, removing one potential limit to further growth of AI systems. More broadly, these results show that neural network training need not be considered a mysterious art, but can be rigorized and\\u00a0systematized.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/how-ai-training-scales<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/how-ai-training-scales<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Fri, 14 Dec 2018 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(746,6,'Quantifying generalization in reinforcement learning','We’re releasing CoinRun, a training environment which provides a metric for an agent’s ability to transfer its experience to novel situations and has already helped clarify a longstanding puzzle in reinforcement learning. CoinRun strikes a desirable balance in complexity: the environment is simpler than traditional platformer games like Sonic the Hedgehog but still poses a worthy generalization challenge for state of the art algorithms.','https://openai.com/index/quantifying-generalization-in-reinforcement-learning','','2018-12-06 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Quantifying generalization in reinforcement learning]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing CoinRun, a training environment which provides a metric for an agent\\u2019s ability to transfer its experience to novel situations and has already helped clarify a\\u00a0longstanding\\u00a0puzzle\\u00a0in reinforcement learning. CoinRun strikes a desirable balance in complexity: the environment is simpler than traditional platformer games like Sonic the Hedgehog but still poses a worthy generalization challenge for state of the art\\u00a0algorithms.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/quantifying-generalization-in-reinforcement-learning<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/quantifying-generalization-in-reinforcement-learning<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 06 Dec 2018 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(747,6,'Spinning Up in Deep RL','We’re releasing Spinning Up in Deep RL, an educational resource designed to let anyone learn to become a skilled practitioner in deep reinforcement learning. Spinning Up consists of crystal-clear examples of RL code, educational exercises, documentation, and tutorials.','https://openai.com/index/spinning-up-in-deep-rl','','2018-11-08 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Spinning Up in Deep RL]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re releasing Spinning Up in Deep RL, an educational resource designed to let anyone learn to become a skilled practitioner in deep reinforcement learning. Spinning Up consists of crystal-clear examples of RL code, educational exercises, documentation, and\\u00a0tutorials.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/spinning-up-in-deep-rl<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/spinning-up-in-deep-rl<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 08 Nov 2018 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',35.33,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(748,6,'Learning concepts with energy functions','We’ve developed an energy-based model that can quickly learn to identify and generate instances of concepts, such as near, above, between, closest, and furthest, expressed as sets of 2d points. Our model learns these concepts after only five demonstrations. We also show cross-domain transfer: we use concepts learned in a 2d particle environment to solve tasks on a 3-dimensional physics-based robot.','https://openai.com/index/learning-concepts-with-energy-functions','','2018-11-07 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Learning concepts with energy functions]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve developed an\\u00a0energy-based model\\u00a0that can quickly learn to identify and generate instances of concepts, such as near, above, between, closest, and furthest, expressed as sets of 2d points. Our model learns these concepts after only five demonstrations. We also show cross-domain transfer: we use concepts learned in a 2d particle environment to solve tasks on a 3-dimensional physics-based\\u00a0robot.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-concepts-with-energy-functions<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-concepts-with-energy-functions<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 07 Nov 2018 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',41.37,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(749,6,'Plan online, learn offline: Efficient learning and exploration via model-based control','','https://openai.com/index/plan-online-learn-offline','','2026-01-31 10:50:34','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Plan online, learn offline: Efficient learning and exploration via model-based control]]><\\/title>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/plan-online-learn-offline<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/plan-online-learn-offline<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 05 Nov 2018 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.50,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:50:34'),
(750,6,'Reinforcement learning with prediction-based rewards','We’ve developed Random Network Distillation (RND), a prediction-based method for encouraging reinforcement learning agents to explore their environments through curiosity, which for the first time exceeds average human performance on Montezuma’s Revenge.','https://openai.com/index/reinforcement-learning-with-prediction-based-rewards','','2018-10-31 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Reinforcement learning with prediction-based rewards]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve developed\\u00a0Random Network Distillation (RND), a prediction-based method for encouraging reinforcement learning agents to explore their environments through curiosity, which for the first time exceeds average human performance on\\u00a0Montezuma\\u2019s Revenge.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/reinforcement-learning-with-prediction-based-rewards<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/reinforcement-learning-with-prediction-based-rewards<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 31 Oct 2018 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',32.52,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(751,6,'Learning complex goals with iterated amplification','We’re proposing an AI safety technique called iterated amplification that lets us specify complicated behaviors and goals that are beyond human scale, by demonstrating how to decompose a task into simpler sub-tasks, rather than by providing labeled data or a reward function. Although this idea is in its very early stages and we have only completed experiments on simple toy algorithmic domains, we’ve decided to present it in its preliminary state because we think it could prove to be a scalable approach to AI safety.','https://openai.com/index/learning-complex-goals-with-iterated-amplification','','2018-10-22 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Learning complex goals with iterated amplification]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019re proposing an AI safety technique called iterated amplification that lets us specify complicated behaviors and goals that are beyond human scale, by demonstrating how to decompose a task into simpler sub-tasks, rather than by providing labeled data or a reward function. Although this idea is in its very early stages and we have only completed experiments on simple toy algorithmic domains, we\\u2019ve decided to present it in its preliminary state because we think it could prove to be a scalable approach to AI\\u00a0safety.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-complex-goals-with-iterated-amplification<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-complex-goals-with-iterated-amplification<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 22 Oct 2018 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',40.00,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(752,6,'OpenAI Scholars 2019: Applications open','We are now accepting applications for our second cohort of OpenAI Scholars, a program where we provide 6–10 stipends and mentorship to individuals from underrepresented groups to study deep learning full-time for 3 months and open-source a project.','https://openai.com/index/openai-scholars-2019','','2018-10-11 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[OpenAI Scholars 2019: Applications open]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We are now accepting applications for our second cohort of OpenAI Scholars, a program where we provide 6\\u201310 stipends and mentorship to individuals from underrepresented groups to study deep learning full-time for 3 months and open-source a project.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2019<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/openai-scholars-2019<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Company]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Thu, 11 Oct 2018 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',31.60,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
