(763,6,'Glow: Better reversible generative models','We introduce Glow, a reversible generative model which uses invertible 1x1 convolutions. It extends previous work on reversible generative models and simplifies the architecture. Our model can generate realistic high resolution images, supports efficient sampling, and discovers features that can be used to manipulate attributes of data. We’re releasing code for the model and an online visualization tool so people can explore and build on these results.','https://openai.com/index/glow','','2018-07-09 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Glow: Better reversible generative models]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We introduce\\u00a0Glow, a reversible generative model which uses invertible 1x1 convolutions. It extends\\u00a0previous\\u00a0work\\u00a0on reversible generative models and simplifies the architecture. Our model can generate realistic high resolution images, supports efficient sampling, and discovers features that can be used to manipulate attributes of data. We\\u2019re releasing code for the model and an online visualization tool so people can explore and build on these\\u00a0results.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/glow<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/glow<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Mon, 09 Jul 2018 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',43.53,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
(764,6,'Learning Montezuma’s Revenge from a single demonstration','We’ve trained an agent to achieve a high score of 74,500 on Montezuma’s Revenge from a single human demonstration, better than any previously published result. Our algorithm is simple: the agent plays a sequence of games starting from carefully chosen states from the demonstration, and learns from them by optimizing the game score using PPO, the same reinforcement learning algorithm that underpins OpenAI Five.','https://openai.com/index/learning-montezumas-revenge-from-a-single-demonstration','','2018-07-04 07:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Learning Montezuma\\u2019s Revenge from a single demonstration]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[We\\u2019ve trained an agent to achieve a high score of 74,500 on\\u00a0Montezuma\\u2019s Revenge\\u00a0from a single human demonstration, better than any previously published result. Our algorithm is simple: the agent plays a sequence of games starting from carefully chosen states from the demonstration, and learns from them by optimizing the game score using\\u00a0PPO, the same reinforcement learning algorithm that underpins\\u00a0OpenAI\\u00a0Five.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-montezumas-revenge-from-a-single-demonstration<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/learning-montezumas-revenge-from-a-single-demonstration<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Research]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Wed, 04 Jul 2018 07:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',39.24,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
