(833,6,'Attacking machine learning with adversarial examples','Adversarial examples are inputs to machine learning models that an attacker has intentionally designed to cause the model to make a mistake; they’re like optical illusions for machines. In this post we’ll show how adversarial examples work across different mediums, and will discuss why securing systems against them can be difficult.','https://openai.com/index/attacking-machine-learning-with-adversarial-examples','','2017-02-24 08:00:00','{\"raw_item\":\"<item>\\n            <title><![CDATA[Attacking machine learning with adversarial examples]]><\\/title>\\n            <description><![CDATA[Adversarial examples are inputs to machine learning models that an attacker has intentionally designed to cause the model to make a mistake; they\\u2019re like optical illusions for machines. In this post we\\u2019ll show how adversarial examples work across different mediums, and will discuss why securing systems against them can be difficult.]]><\\/description>\\n            <link>https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/attacking-machine-learning-with-adversarial-examples<\\/link>\\n            <guid isPermaLink=\\\"true\\\">https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/attacking-machine-learning-with-adversarial-examples<\\/guid>\\n            <category><![CDATA[Safety & Alignment]]><\\/category>\\n            <pubDate>Fri, 24 Feb 2017 08:00:00 GMT<\\/pubDate>\\n        <\\/item>\",\"source_name\":\"OpenAI Blog\"}',39.17,NULL,0.00,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'pending',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-31 10:47:37','2026-01-31 10:47:37'),
